gomodel:SYNGO_5451  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The established heterotrimeric (KIF3A/KIF3B/KAP3) complex (KIF3 complex) is here shown to transport NR2 into dendritic spines (Fig. 7E).\n\nFigure 1: KIF3B binds to the NR2A complex and both interact with all KIF3 complex subunits as expected.\n\nFigure 2: KIF3B is essential for the postsynaptic localization of NR2A and NR2B in hippocampal neurons.\n\nFigure 3: KIF3B transports NR2A, but not NR2B.\n\nFigure 7: The expression of KIF3B, but not mutated KIF3B, restores spine morphology and NR2A surface expression.. Experimental description: Results: \"Immunoblotting of crude extracts of the Kif3b+/- mouse brains ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5451" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

